   attacks on a ship with one, two and three pirate ships have been
   prepared and analyzed. Such a system in its own nature is very complex.
   It consists of a continuous portion (Continuous Systems), ie. movement
   of the attacked ship, pirate ship motion and movement naval vessel /
   helicopter (change speed, distance), and the Discrete Event Systems, ie.
   commencing of attack, sending distress. Analyzed the factors that affect
   the safety of navigation of the ship through the area of increased risk
   from possible pirate attacks. The mentioned are typical indicators and
   studied ways of improving the safety in order to finally demonstrate how
   developed applications time dynamics of pirate attacks leads to the
   optimal solution of planning navigation ships through the pirate areas.},
