   modeled with Petri nets. The secret behavior of a system is defined as a
   set of states. More precisely, two state-based opacity properties are
   considered: current-state opacity and initial-state opacity. We show
   that both current-state and initial-state opacity problems in bounded
   Petri nets can be efficiently solved by using a compact representation
   of the reachability graph, called basis reachability graph (BRG). This
   approach is practically efficient since the exhaustive enumeration of
   the reachability space can be avoided.},
