   paper, we investigate the enforcement of opacity using insertion
   functions which insert additional events if necessary to modify the
   output of the system. Inspired by the existing insertion mechanisms, we
   propose a mechanism named k-memory-embedded insertion mechanism for the
   enforcement of opacity. In our k-memory-embedded insertion mechanism,
