   infinite-step opacity is a property such that the visit of a secret
   state cannot be inferred by an intruder at any instance along the entire
   observation trajectory, while strong k-step opacity is a property such
   that the visit of a secret state cannot be inferred within k steps after
   the visit. We propose two information structures called an 8-step
   recognizer and a k-step recognizer to verify these two properties. The
   complexities of our algorithms to verify strong infinite- and k-step
   opacity are O(2(2.vertical bar X vertical bar) . vertical bar E-o
